#  1. Write a Program for Inventory Updating using a structure having (char name [20], float rate, int  qty, float price).

## a) Ask the user to enter one record (keep price blank). Create a function to calculate the price = rate * qty and store it for the record. Also, ask the user for updating the rate and qty and  update the record and recalculate the price. Display all the details of the record.

```Cpp

#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

typedef struct {
   char name[20];
   float rate, price;
   int qty;
}
Inventory;

void Calculate (Inventory &a) {
   a.price = (float) a.rate * a.qty;
   return ;
}

void Display (Inventory &a) {
   cout<<"Name: "<<a.name<<endl
       <<"Rate: "<<a.rate<<endl
       <<"Quantity: "<<a.qty<<endl
       <<"Price: "<<a.price<<endl
       <<endl;
}

void EnterInformation(Inventory &a) {
   cout<<"Name: ";
   cin >> a.name;
   cout<<"Rate: ";
   cin >> a.rate;
   cout<<"Quantity: ";
   cin >> a.qty;
   cout<<endl;
}

int main() {
   int choice;
   Inventory a;
   while (true) {
       cout<<"1. Input Information"<<endl
           <<"2. Display Information"<<endl
           <<"3. Quit"<<endl;
       cout<<">> ";
       cin>>choice;
       switch (choice) {
           case 1:
               EnterInformation(a);
               Calculate(a);
               break;
           case 2:
               Display(a);
               break;
           case 3:
               cout<<"Quitting..."<<endl;
               return 0;
           default:
               cout<<"Invalid choice"<<endl;
       }
   }
   return 0;
}

```

## b) Rewrite part (a) of the program to make a single structure variable and a single pointer to  structure. Assign the address of the structure variable to the pointer and enter one record  through the pointer and update the record using pointer.

```Cpp


#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

typedef struct {
   char name[20];
   float rate, price;
   int qty;
}
Inventory;

void Calculate (Inventory &a) {
   a.price = (float) a.rate * a.qty;
   return ;
}

void Display (Inventory &a) {
   cout<<"Name: "<<a.name<<endl
       <<"Rate: "<<a.rate<<endl
       <<"Quantity: "<<a.qty<<endl
       <<"Price: "<<a.price<<endl
       <<endl;
}

void EnterInformation(Inventory &a) {
   cout<<"Name: ";
   cin >> a.name;
   cout<<"Rate: ";
   cin >> a.rate;
   cout<<"Quantity: ";
   cin >> a.qty;
   cout<<endl;
}

int main() {
   int choice;
   Inventory a;
   Inventory *ptr = &a;
   while (true) {
       cout<<"1. Input Information"<<endl
           <<"2. Display Information"<<endl
           <<"3. Quit"<<endl;
       cout<<">> ";
       cin>>choice;
       switch (choice) {
           case 1:
               EnterInformation(*ptr);
               Calculate(*ptr);
               break;
           case 2:
               Display(*ptr);
               break;
           case 3:
               cout<<"Quitting..."<<endl;
               return 0;
           default:
               cout<<"Invalid choice"<<endl;
       }
   }
   return 0;
}
```

## c) Rewrite the part (a) of the program for Inventory Updating; this time creating an array of  structures so that n records can be kept. Ask the user to enter number of records and then  details of all the records. Finally, for updating, ask the user to enter the record number [array  subscript] to be updated with the new rate and qty and recalculate the price and display either  all records or only the updated record.

```Cpp

#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

typedef struct {
   char name[20];
   float rate, price;
   int qty;
}
Inventory;

void Calculate (Inventory &a) {
   a.price = (float) a.rate * a.qty;
   return ;
}

void Display (Inventory &a) {
   cout<<"Name: "<<a.name<<endl
       <<"Rate: "<<a.rate<<endl
       <<"Quantity: "<<a.qty<<endl
       <<"Price: "<<a.price<<endl
       <<endl;
}

void EnterInformation(Inventory &a) {
   cout<<"Name: ";
   cin >> a.name;
   cout<<"Rate: ";
   cin >> a.rate;
   cout<<"Quantity: ";
   cin >> a.qty;
   cout<<endl;
}

int main() {
   int choice, n, curr;
   cout<<"Number of records to be kept: ";
   cin >> n;
   Inventory arr[n];
   for (int i = 0; i < n; i++){
       cout<<"Record "<<i+1<<":"<<endl;
       EnterInformation(arr[i]);
       Calculate(arr[i]);
   }
   while (true) {
       cout<<"1. Update Information"<<endl
           <<"2. Display Information"<<endl
           <<"3. Quit"<<endl;
       cout<<">> ";
       cin>>choice;
       switch (choice) {
           case 1:
               cout<<"Choose Record (1 - "<< n <<"): ";
               cin >> curr;
               --curr;
               EnterInformation(arr[curr]);
               Calculate(arr[curr]);
               break;
           case 2:
               cout<<"Choose Record (1 - "<< n <<"): ";
               cin >> curr;
               --curr;
               Display(arr[curr]);
               break;
           case 3:
               cout<<"Quitting..."<<endl;
               return 0;
           default:
               cout<<"Invalid choice"<<endl;
       }
   }
   return 0;
}


```

# 2. Write a program to find Fibonacci series using an array

```Cpp

#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

int main() {
   int n, i;
   cout << "Enter the number of terms: ";
   cin >> n;
   int fib[n];
   fib[0] = 0;
   fib[1] = 1;
   cout << "Fibonacci series: " << fib[0] << " " << fib[1] << " ";
   for (i = 2; i < n; i++) {
       fib[i] = fib[i-1] + fib[i-2];
       cout << fib[i] << " ";
   }
   cout<<endl;
   return 0;
}


```

```Cpp

#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

int main() {
   int n;
   cout << "Taking input for size of matrix (N x N):\n Enter N:";
   cin >> n;
   int arr[n][n];
   cout<<"Taking input for elements of matrix:\n";
   for (int i = 0; i < n; i++){
       for (int j = 0; j < n; j++){
           cout<<"Element "<<i+1<<','<<j+1<<": ";
           cin >> arr[i][j];
       }
   }
   cout<<"Displaying matrix: "<<endl;
   for (int i = 0; i < n; i++){
       for (int j = 0; j < n; j++){
           cout<<arr[i][j]<<"  ";
       }
       cout<<endl;
   }
   for (int i = 0; i < n; i++){
       for (int j = 0; j < n; j++){
           if (arr[i][j] != arr[j][i]) {
               cout<<"Matrix is not symmetric"<<endl;
               return 0;
           }
       }
   }
   cout<<"Matrix is symmetric"<<endl;
   return 0;
}
```
